<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FF09FABDA231FA67" bold="true" box="[199,316,1397,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FE8CFABEA2F1FA67" authority="Gyulai, 2018" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[322,508,1397,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FE8CFABEA2F1FA67" box="[322,508,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Xestia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FDCCFABDA133FA67" bold="true" box="[514,574,1397,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="399D57ADA940FF86FDCCFABDA133FA67" box="[514,574,1397,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="88E12A41A940FF86FD82FABEA1C9FA67" box="[588,708,1398,1421]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,266,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,261,1808]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 2. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 3. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 4. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 5. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 6. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), male, China, Sichuan (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608055/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Figs 1, 2, 3</figureCitation>
) is a medium sized species, similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FBAEFABEA691FA67" authority="(Boursin, 1963)" authorityName="Boursin" authorityYear="1963" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1120,1436,1397,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FBAEFABEA7E1FA67" box="[1120,1260,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="744B4B35A940FF86FB35FABEA699FA67" author="Boursin, Ch." box="[1275,1428,1398,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" pagination="9 - 107" refId="ref1394" refString="Boursin, Ch. (1963) Die Noctuinae Arten (Agrotinae vulgo sensu) aus Dr. h. c. H. Hone's China-Ausbeuten. Forschungsberichte des Landes Nordhein-Westfalen, 1170, 9 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 663 - 07024 - 5" type="journal article" year="1963">Boursin, 1963</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="88E12A41A940FF86FF50FA50A3F3FA45" box="[158,254,1432,1455]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,266,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,261,1808]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 2. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 3. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 4. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 5. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 6. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), male, China, Sichuan (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608055/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Figs 4-5</figureCitation>
), from which it is best distinguished by the size, some of the external features and the study of the male genitalia. The distinguishing external features are as follows: the new species is significantly larger than 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FAC3FA73A691FA38" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1293,1436,1466,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FAC3FA73A691FA38" box="[1293,1436,1466,1490]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="D7229B21A940FF86FF50FA16A21AFA1F" box="[158,279,1502,1525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="29.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="28.0">28–30 mm</quantity>
, versus 
<quantity id="D7229B21A940FF86FEBFFA16A2E6FA1F" box="[369,491,1502,1525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="25.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="24.0">24–26 mm</quantity>
); the male antennae bipectinate versus finely ciliate in the 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FBBDFA16A60FFA1F" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1139,1282,1501,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FBBDFA16A60FFA1F" box="[1139,1282,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the forewing apex is more elongate; the ground colour of the forewings, including the basal area, is darker and greyish,, versus brownish in 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FED2F9EBA2A4F9D0" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[284,425,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FED2F9EBA2A4F9D0" box="[284,425,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the basal area conspicuously whitish. Hindwings of 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FBDEF9EBA793F9D0" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[1040,1182,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FBDEF9EBA793F9D0" box="[1040,1182,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also darker, greyish and not light brown; the orbicular stigmata are elongate, larger than in 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FC04F98EA756F9B7" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[970,1115,1605,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FC04F98EA756F9B7" box="[970,1115,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and without the fine white encircling.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="106536C4A940FF86FF09F943A01EF8C7" blockId="0.[151,1437,1224,2010]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
Another somewhat similar, but not related species is 
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FD36F942A0E5F948" box="[760,1000,1674,1698]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Brachylomia pygmaea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="744B4B35A940FF86FC38F943A78AF948" author="Draudt, M." box="[1014,1159,1675,1698]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" pagination="1 - 174" refId="ref1480" refString="Draudt, M. (1950) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Agrotiden-Fauna Chinas aus den Ausbeuten Dr. H. Hone's. (Beitrag zur Fauna Sinica) Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 40 (1), 1 - 174." type="journal article" year="1950">Draudt, 1950</bibRefCitation>
), (
<figureCitation id="88E12A41A940FF86FB6FF943A7EEF948" box="[1185,1251,1675,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,266,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,261,1808]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 2. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 3. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 4. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 5. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 6. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), male, China, Sichuan (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608055/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FB38F943A689F948" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[1270,1412,1674,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FB38F943A689F948" box="[1270,1412,1674,1698]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat larger (
<quantity id="D7229B21A940FF86FE96F966A2C2F92F" box="[344,463,1710,1733]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="29.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="28.0">28–30 mm</quantity>
, versus 
<quantity id="D7229B21A940FF86FDE9F966A190F92F" box="[551,669,1710,1733]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="26.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="25.0">25–27 mm</quantity>
) and differs significantly in the more elongate forewing apex; in being much darker and greyish (not yellowish); in the more elongate orbicular and reniform stigmata; the much darker hindwings and darker undersides of all the wings, with the conspicuous presence of the discal spot in the hindwing, which is not visible in the whitish hindwing of 
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FD43F8DEA01EF8C7" box="[653,787,1814,1837]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">B. pygmaea.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="106536C4A940FF87FF09F8F0A0AAFF3B" blockId="0.[151,1437,1224,2010]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,151,209]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="446" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
In the male genitalia, the differences between 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FD7BF8F1A049F8A5" authority="Gyulai, 2018" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[693,836,1847,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FD7BF8F1A049F8A5" box="[693,836,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FC85F8F0A08AF8BA" bold="true" box="[843,903,1848,1872]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="399D57ADA940FF86FC85F8F0A08AF8BA" box="[843,903,1848,1872]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FC72F8F1A744F8A5" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[956,1097,1847,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FC72F8F1A744F8A5" box="[956,1097,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found in the shape and size of the uncus, harpe, cucullus, aedeagus and in the configuration of the vesica. 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FC25F893A776F898" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[1003,1147,1882,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FC25F893A776F898" box="[1003,1147,1882,1906]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="88E12A41A940FF86FB44F893A7E7F898" box="[1162,1258,1883,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[242,1336,336,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,330,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. 7. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4934 (PGM); 8. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4904 (PGM); 9. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP2376 (PGM); 10. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP4905 (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608057/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) differs from 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FA4BF893A20BF87F" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FA4BF893A20BF87F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="88E12A41A940FF86FED9F8B6A254F87F" box="[279,345,1918,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[242,1336,336,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,330,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. 7. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4934 (PGM); 8. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4904 (PGM); 9. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP2376 (PGM); 10. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP4905 (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608057/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) by its strong, lanceolate, apically hooked uncus (it is spatulate and broadly flattened apically in 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A940FF86FA4BF8B6A20BF85D" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A940FF86FA4BF8B6A20BF85D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); larger, longer and not falciform harpe, and larger cucullus. Additionally, the broadly tubular vesica, recurved dorsad with a robust, elongate, sclerotized bar, deriving from the medio-dorsal section of aedeagus, are diagnostic characters and provide easy recognition of the new species relative to 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A941FF87FC0DFF50A758FF45" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[963,1109,151,175]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FC0DFF50A758FF45" box="[963,1109,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the thin, elongate sclerotised bar is positioned ventrad and the vesica also recurved ventrad.
</paragraph>
<caption id="44A5664CA941FF87FF59F8ECA2B8F878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608055/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" startId="1.[151,258,1828,1850]" targetBox="[156,1436,266,1787]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="106536C4A941FF87FF59F8ECA2B8F878" blockId="1.[151,1436,1828,1938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FF59F8ECA23CF8D0" bold="true" box="[151,305,1828,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">FIGURES 1–6.</emphasis>
Adults. 1. 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A941FF87FE57F8EDA132F8D0" authority="Gyulai, 2018" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[409,575,1829,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FE57F8EDA132F8D0" box="[409,575,1829,1850]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Xestia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FD8BF8ECA176F8D0" bold="true" box="[581,635,1828,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="399D57ADA941FF87FD8BF8ECA176F8D0" box="[581,635,1828,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 2. 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A941FF87FBD2F8EDA7CEF8D0" authority="Gyulai, 2018" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[1052,1219,1829,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FBD2F8EDA7CEF8D0" box="[1052,1219,1829,1850]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Xestia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FB06F8ECA7F3F8D0" bold="true" box="[1224,1278,1828,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="399D57ADA941FF87FB06F8ECA7F3F8D0" box="[1224,1278,1828,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 3. 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A941FF87FE5BF88AA136F8BD" authority="Gyulai, 2018" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[405,571,1858,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FE5BF88AA136F8BD" box="[405,571,1858,1879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Xestia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FD8FF88AA17AF8B2" bold="true" box="[577,631,1858,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="399D57ADA941FF87FD8FF88AA17AF8B2" box="[577,631,1858,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 4. 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A941FF87FBD7F88AA650F8BD" authority="(Boursin, 1963)" authorityName="Boursin" authorityYear="1963" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1049,1373,1858,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FBD7F88AA7B2F8BD" box="[1049,1215,1858,1879]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Xestia diagrapha</emphasis>
(Boursin, 1963)
</taxonomicName>
, male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 5. 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A941FF87FE57F8A8A1EDF89F" authority="(Boursin, 1963)" authorityName="Boursin" authorityYear="1963" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[409,736,1888,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FE57F8A8A14DF89F" box="[409,576,1888,1909]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Xestia diagrapha</emphasis>
(Boursin, 1963)
</taxonomicName>
, male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 6. 
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A941FF87FBE6F8A8A60CF89F" box="[1064,1281,1888,1909]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Brachylomia pygmaea</emphasis>
(Draudt, 1950), male, China, Sichuan (PGM).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="106536C4A942FF84FF09FF50A72DFEFD" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
The male genitalia (the presence of the pollex and harpe, the shape of the valvae, the lack of the corona in the cucullus) of 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A942FF84FEECFF72A2B9FF3B" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[290,436,185,209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A942FF84FEECFF72A2B9FF3B" box="[290,436,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly indicate that it belongs to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A942FF84FC1CFF72A732FF3B" box="[978,1087,186,209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A942FF84FC1CFF72A732FF3B" box="[978,1087,186,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Noctuinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A942FF84FB5BFF72A61BFF3B" box="[1173,1302,186,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">B. pygmaea</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="88E12A41A942FF84FAE6FF72A675FF3B" box="[1320,1400,186,209]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[242,1336,336,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,330,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. 7. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4934 (PGM); 8. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4904 (PGM); 9. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP2376 (PGM); 10. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP4905 (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608057/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) is similar only superficially; the male genitalia (the absence of the pollex, the short sacculus, the presence of a short corona in the cucullus) in this latter species reflect its placement in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="D7DA4D47A942FF84FC60FF37A715FEFD" box="[942,1048,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Xyleninae">
<emphasis id="22AEEAD6A942FF84FC60FF37A715FEFD" box="[942,1048,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Xyleninae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="44A5664CA942FF84FF59F8A2A7E3F828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608057/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" startId="2.[151,258,1898,1920]" targetBox="[242,1336,336,1874]" targetPageId="2">
